race.description: Community Bank Drouin & District Maiden Plate
race.comment: HEADBANGER (2) has the benefit of race experience which should take her a long way. She was formerly with the Waterhouse & Bott yard, running well in a 2yo race at Hawkesbury back in April. Can't see her going backyard under Grahame Begg and she can make a winning start for the new yard. The majority of the dangers are on debut. NIMCHA (5) is a filly by Lonhro for the Freedman yard who has won a recent trial leading in. Must respect the top yard and connections, expect she goes well. YELLOWJACKET (11) is an I Am Invincible filly on debut for the Stokes yard on her home deck. She's jumped out well enough to be a serious player. MISS MARANDA (4) is a filly by Written Tycoon on debut for the Moody & Coleman yard. She's won a jumpout here and draws ideally. Keep safe.
